content: Paid for this app. Won't get past the opening screen on Android 10. Can't get a refund because the email address is out of commission. Went with the Hornady free app and had good results. Don't get this if you're using Android.

So got this and used it during a long range class put on by Snipers Hide. Running on my older S5 Active, it was pretty damn accurate. I usually only needed some minor tweaking to get solid hits at 1000. The day I got a new S9, the program would not run. Thought I was screwed. Read thru the reviews, and a user said you had to enable all the permissions... seeing it was dated in 2019 I figured I'd try it. IT WORKED! Manually turning on permissions in app settings worked for me.
Bought a Samsung A 8. Wont even open up
YOU MUST GO INTO SETTINGS AND ENABLE ALL PERMISSIONS FOR APP TO OPEN.

I'm a long term ballistics applications user and from 6 aps I currently have installed on my phone TRASOL is the slowest. Have way to many bugs for a release, from my point of view is at beta tester level and is not wothing 40$ the initial price. As developer support. ...slow, even if users report bugs and problems and a new version was released some reported bug as azimuth error is not solved yet. I will recommend this app when will grew to an mature an acomplished app, but not now.
But still has quite a few bugs, like the compass..
This is a great app and it's maturing into one of the best ballistics apps out there.
They took input from users and really improved to the next level.

Awasome app! Most accurate solutions and easy to use. Would like some more features but it's awasome.

I'll admit I'm a DTA fanboy, bought their first run of the SRS. With that in mind, I've tried and paid good money for numerous ballistic calcs, both for PC, iPhone, and Droid. I can say without a doubt, this is the cleanest app I've encountered. Will update as I learn more fun things to do. Thanks DTA, or whatever you renamed to!
